&lt;Elders Resources Ltd> said itstwo-for-seven convertible unsecured notes issue will raise161.32 mln dlrs for group expansion and development.    The 46.99 pct-owned Elders IXL Ltd &lt;ELXA.S> offshootannounced the issue at 2.50 dlrs each with its first-halfresults statement.    The group lifted net earnings to 16.93 mln dlrs in the halfended December 31 from 5.47 mln a year earlier when it wasstill in its formative stages.    The 8.0 pct notes are convertible to one share on May 1 andNovember 1 of each year from next November. Reuter&#3;